{{inline|date=July 2013}}
'''Kenneth Desmond Colbung''' [[Order of Australia|AM]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (2 September 1931 – 13 January 2010), also known by his indigenous name '''Nundjan Djiridjarkan''', was an [[Australian Aborigines|Aboriginal Australian]] leader who became prominent in the 1960s.  He was awarded an [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] and an [[Order of Australia|AM]] for his service to the Aboriginal community. 

He died after a short illness on 12 January 2010. He was 78.<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2010/01/13/2791595.htm?site=perth Prominent Aboriginal elder Ken Colbung dies], [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]], 13 January 2010.</ref>

